!import-table --CRIT_Bludgeon --show
!import-table-item --CRIT_Bludgeon --Smashed off balance! Roll damage as normal and the next attack against the creature has advantage. --2 --
!import-table-item --CRIT_Bludgeon --Good hit! Do not roll your damage dice, instead deal the maximum result possible with those dice. --3 --
!import-table-item --CRIT_Bludgeon --Sent reeling! Do not roll your damage dice, instead deal the maximum result possible with those dice and push the creature up to 15 feet in any direction. --2 --
!import-table-item --CRIT_Bludgeon --Great hit! Roll your damage dice twice and add them together. --3 --
!import-table-item --CRIT_Bludgeon --Take a seat! Roll damage dice twice and add them together and the creature is knocked prone. --2 --
!import-table-item --CRIT_Bludgeon --Rocked and rolled! Roll damage dice twice and add them together, push the creature up to 15 feet away, and the creature is knocked prone. --3 --
!import-table-item --CRIT_Bludgeon --Grievous injury! Deal the maximum amount of damage from your normal damage dice then roll your damage dice and add the result. Then roll on the Minor Injury chart. If the creature is unarmored or wearing light armor receive a Wound point instead. --2 --
!import-table-item --CRIT_Bludgeon --Crushed! Deal the twice maximum result of your damage dice and receive a Wound point. --1 --
!import-table-item --CRIT_Bludgeon --Splat! Deal the maximum result of your damage dice twice, the creature is stunned until the end of your next turn, and receive a Wound point. --1 --
